1 Sec. 4. Section 2-1095, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
2 amended to read:
3 2-1095 (1) All nursery stock distributors that distribute any
4 nursery stock that they grow shall apply for a certification an
5 additional inspection for the certification of the Nebraska-grown nursery
6 stock as provided in this section. The nursery stock distributor shall
7 receive apply for such certification inspection of the Nebraska-grown
8 nursery stock as part of the application for the nursery stock
9 distributor license described in section 2-1091.01.
10 (2)(a) Applications for certification inspection of Nebraska-grown
11 nursery stock that are due on January 1 pursuant to section 2-1091.01 and
12 are not received prior to February 1 and initial applications not
13 received prior to beginning of distribution shall be considered
14 delinquent. Such applications shall be accompanied with the have an
15 inspection fee that is as set forth in section 2-1091.02.
16 (b) Inspection time shall be determined based on any portion of a
17 whole hour and shall include the driving time to and from the location of
18 the inspection in addition to the time spent conducting the inspection,
19 and the mileage charge shall be for the purpose of inspection.
20 (3) Each nursery stock distributor shall post signs delineating
21 sections of all growing areas. A section shall be not larger than five
22 acres.
23 (4) All growing areas within the state shall be inspected by the
24 department at least once per year for certification and compliance with
25 the Plant Protection and Plant Pest Act.
26 (5) Following the certification inspection of Nebraska-grown nursery
27 stock, the department shall provide a copy of the plant inspection report
28 to the nursery stock distributor specifying any area of the nursery from
29 which nursery stock cannot be distributed or any plants which may not be
30 distributed as nursery stock. When deemed necessary to maintain
31 compliance with the purposes of the Plant Protection and Plant Pest Act,
-9-

LB947 LB947
2026 2026
1 the department shall require the nursery stock distributor to withdraw
2 from distribution any variety or amount of nursery stock. A reinspection
3 may be conducted by the department at the nursery stock distributor's
4 request and cost. The department may also reinspect to determine
5 compliance with the act. To determine the cost of any reinspection, the
6 department shall use fees as outlined in subsection (2) of this section.
7 The nursery stock distributor shall comply with the recommendations of
8 the department as to the treatment or destruction of nursery stock.
9 (6) The department may require the treatment or destruction of any
10 nursery stock that is infested or infected with plant pests, nonviable,
11 damaged, or desiccated to the point of not being reasonably capable of
12 growth.
13 (7) Any nursery stock on which a withdrawal-from-distribution order
14 has been issued shall be released for distribution only by authorized
15 department employees or after written permission has been obtained from
16 the department. Each nursery stock distributor shall promptly report to
17 the department, in writing, the amount and type of plants treated or
18 destroyed under requirements on withdrawal-from-distribution orders. The
19 department may withhold a license or certification of Nebraska-grown
20 nursery stock until conditions have been met by the nursery stock
21 distributor as specified in the plant inspection report or any other
22 order issued by the department. A certification of Nebraska-grown stock
23 may be issued covering portions of the nursery which are not infested or
24 infected if the nursery stock distributor agrees to treat, destroy, or
25 remove as specified by the department those plants found to be infested
26 or infected.
27 Sec. 5. Section 2-10,117, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
28 amended to read:
29 2-10,117 All money received from any source pursuant to the Plant
30 Protection and Plant Pest Act and section 81-2,162.23 shall be remitted
31 by the department to the State Treasurer and by the State Treasurer
-10-

LB947 LB947
2026 2026
1 credited to the Plant Protection and Plant Pest Cash Fund which is hereby
2 created. The fund also shall include funds transferred pursuant to
3 section 81-201.05. The fund shall be used by the department to aid in
4 defraying the expenses of administering the act. Any money in the fund
5 available for investment shall be invested by the state investment
6 officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital Expansion Act and the Nebraska
7 State Funds Investment Act.
8 Sec. 6. Section 2-1808, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
9 amended to read:
10 2-1808 The State Treasurer is hereby directed to establish and set
11 up in the treasury of the State of Nebraska a fund to be known as the
12 Nebraska Potato Development Fund, to which fund shall be credited, for
13 the uses and purposes of the Nebraska Potato Development Act and its
14 enforcement, all taxes and fees collected by the Department of
15 Agriculture. After appropriation, the Director of Administrative
16 Services, upon receipt of proper vouchers approved by the director of the
17 department, shall issue his or her warrants on such funds and the State
18 Treasurer shall pay the same out of the money credited to the fund. Any
19 money in the fund available for investment shall be invested by the state
20 investment officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital Expansion Act and the
21 Nebraska State Funds Investment Act. The fund terminates on July 1, 2026,
22 and the State Treasurer shall transfer any money in the fund to the Plant
23 Protection and Plant Pest Cash Fund as soon as administratively
24 practicable.
25 Sec. 7. Section 2-2634, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
26 amended to read:
27 2-2634 (1) As a condition to registration or renewal of registration
28 as required by sections 2-2628 to 2-2633, an applicant shall pay to the
29 department a fee of two hundred one hundred sixty dollars for each
30 pesticide to be registered, except that the fee may be increased or
31 decreased by rules and regulations adopted and promulgated pursuant to
-11-

LB947 LB947
2026 2026
1 the Pesticide Act. In no event shall such fee exceed two hundred fifty
2 two hundred ten dollars for each pesticide to be registered.
3 (2) All fees collected under subsection (1) of this section shall be
4 remitted to the State Treasurer for credit as follows:
5 (a) Fifty Thirty dollars of such fee to the Noxious Weed Cash Fund
6 as provided in section 2-958;
7 (b) Fifty dollars of such fee to the Buffer Strip Incentive Fund as
8 provided in section 2-5106;
9 (c) Fifty-five dollars of such fee to the Natural Resources Water
10 Quality Fund; and
11 (d) The remainder of such fee to the Pesticide Administrative Cash
12 Fund.
13 (3) If a person fails to apply for renewal of registration before
14 January 1 of any year, such person, as a condition to renewal, shall pay
15 a late registration fee equal to twenty-five percent of the fee due and
16 owing per month, not to exceed one hundred percent, for each product to
17 be renewed in addition to the renewal fee. The purpose of the late
18 registration fee is to cover the administrative costs associated with
19 collecting fees, and all money collected as a late registration fee shall
20 be remitted to the State Treasurer for credit to the Pesticide
21 Administrative Cash Fund.
22 Sec. 8. Section 81-201, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
23 amended to read:
24 81-201 The Department of Agriculture may: shall have power
25 (1) Encourage to encourage and promote, in every practicable manner,
26 the interest of agriculture;
27 (2) Promote to promote methods of conducting the industry of
28 agriculture with a view to increasing the production and facilitating the
29 distribution thereof at the least cost;
30 (3) Collect to collect and publish statistics relating to the
31 production and marketing of agricultural products, so far as such
-12-

LB947 LB947
2026 2026
1 statistical information may be of value to the agricultural and allied
2 interests of the state, and to cooperate with the federal government in
3 the matter of collecting and publishing such statistical information;
4 (4) Distribute or dispose of any remaining to publish and distribute
5 the Weeds of the Great Plains books book and supplemental inserts thereto
6 that are in the possession of the department. By January 1, 2027, the
7 State Treasurer shall transfer all money in the Weed Book Cash Fund to
8 the Noxious Weed Cash Fund. , for sale and distribution to the public.
9 All money collected from the sale of the publications shall be remitted
10 to the State Treasurer and credited to the Noxious Weed Cash Fund as
11 provided in section 81-201.05;
12 (5) Inquire to inquire into the causes of contagious, infectious,
13 and communicable diseases among domestic animals and the means for the
14 prevention and cure of the same;
15 (6) Execute to execute and enforce all laws relating to matters
16 within its jurisdiction and to adopt necessary rules and regulations for
17 the administration and enforcement of such laws;
18 (7) Employ to employ special investigators who shall be appointed
19 deputy state sheriffs by the Governor and who shall, upon qualifying for
20 such office, possess all the powers which attach to such office, except
21 that their powers and duties shall be restricted to the enforcement of
22 the laws of the State of Nebraska within the jurisdiction of the
23 Department of Agriculture;
24 (8) Perform to perform laboratory testing services as provided in
25 section 81-2,293; and
26 (9) Enforce to enforce the Foreign-owned Real Estate National
27 Security Act.
28 Sec. 9. Original sections 2-1091, 2-1091.02, 2-1095, 2-10,117,
29 2-1808, 2-2634, and 81-201, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, and
30 section 2-958, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement, 2024, are
31 repealed.
